The paper deals with algorithms for sampling rows of a matrix, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science such as data analysis, machine learning, and signal processing. The use of statistical leverage scores and reweighted matrices suggests a connection to information theory and machine learning (cs.IT and cs.LG). The focus on preserving p-norms of the product with vectors suggests a connection to numerical analysis and scientific computing (cs.NA). Finally, the use of input sparsity time algorithms suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and possibly also to computational complexity theory (cs.SI).
